Remove duplicated items from array of items, which each items is also associative array.
===

Function implementation:
```php
<?php
/**
 * Removes duplicates from multidimensional associative array by key.
 * Ignores items from resulting array with the same key.
 * If key is not set in the item, that item will be ignored from resulting array.
 * @param array  $array array of associative arrays with key.
 * @param string $key   associative array key to check for duplicates.
 * @return array resulting array of associative arrays.
 */
function array_unique_by_key($array,$key)
{
	$tmp   =[];
	$result=[];
	foreach($array as $item)
	{
		if(!isset($item[$key]))
			continue;
		if(!in_array($item[$key],$tmp))
		{
			$tmp[]   =$item[$key];
			$result[]=$item;
		}
	}
	return $result;
}
```

