Clone/copy javascript object (not DOM object)
===

Note that the .clone() method in jQuery only clones DOM elements.
In order to clone JavaScript objects, you can do:

```javascript
// Shallow copy
var newObject = jQuery.extend({}, oldObject);

// Deep copy
var newObject = jQuery.extend(true, {}, oldObject);
```

Original answer is [here](http://stackoverflow.com/a/122704).

