# Helper class to work with parameters without DB

If we omit `$param` it will return all values & descriptions as associative array, which is ready to pass to `CHtml::dropDownList()`.

If we specify `$param` as string (name), it will return parameter value by name.

If we specify `$param` as integer (value), it will return parameter description by value (index).

```php
<?php
class P
{
	public static function comment( $param = null )
	{
		$items = [
			0 => [ 'disabled', Yii::t( 'zr', 'Disabled' ), ],
			1 => [ 'allowed', Yii::t( 'zr', 'Allowed' ), ],
		];
		return self::handle( $items, $param );
	}

	public static function contentStatus( $param = null )
	{
		$items = [
			0 => [ 'draft', Yii::t( 'zr', 'Draft' ), ],
			1 => [ 'published', Yii::t( 'zr', 'Published' ), ],
			2 => [ 'deleted', Yii::t( 'zr', 'Deleted' ), ],
		];
		return self::handle( $items, $param );
	}

	public static function language( $param = null )
	{
		$items = [
			1 => [ 'ru', Yii::t( 'zr', 'Russian' ), ],
			2 => [ 'uz', Yii::t( 'zr', 'Uzbek' ), ],
			3 => [ 'en', Yii::t( 'zr', 'English' ), ],
		];
		return self::handle( $items, $param );
	}

	public static function status( $param = null )
	{
		$items = [
			0 => [ 'disabled', Yii::t( 'zr', 'Disabled' ), ],
			1 => [ 'active', Yii::t( 'zr', 'Active' ), ],
		];
		return self::handle( $items, $param );
	}

	/**
	 * Handle parameters.
	 * @param array           $items parameters list [param_value=>[param_name, param_description], ...]
	 * @param int|null|string $param null to return list of [param_value=>param_description,...],
	 *                               param name string to return value,
	 *                               param value to return param description.
	 * @return int|null|string param value, list of param value and description or param description by value.
	 */
	private static function handle( $items, $param )
	{
		if ( is_null( $param ) ) // return [value => description,...]
		{
			$res = null;
			foreach ( $items as $key => $val )
				$res[ $key ] = $val[ 1 ];
			return $res;
		}
		elseif ( is_numeric( $param ) )
			return $items[ $param ][ 1 ];
		elseif ( is_string( $param ) ) // return value
		{
			foreach ( $items as $key => $val )
				if ( $param == $val[ 0 ] )
					return $key;
			return null;
		}
	}
}
```

Usage example

```php
<?php
// Get all content statuses and show in drop down
echo CHtml::dropDownList('contentstatus', false, P::contentStatus(), ['class' => 'form-control']);

// Get content status value by name
echo P::contentStatus('published'); // 1

// Get content status description by value
echo P::contentStatus((int)1); // 'Published'
