# Inheritance example in JavaScript

For example, we create `Person` class:
```js
// Person class
function Person(options, data){
	this._default_options={
		option1: 'default_val_1',
		option2: 'default_val_2'
	};
	this.options=$.extend({}, this._default_options, options); // override default options if specified
	// some common properties
	this.first_name='';
	this.last_name='';
	this.age=0;
};

Person.prototype.method_1=function(data){
	// process data, do some useful operations
	return this; // support chains
};
