Initialize `$approveJs` variable before `CGridView` widget:

```php
<?php
$approveJs = 'js:function(__event)
{
	__event.preventDefault(); // disable default action

	var $this = $(this), // link/button
		confirm_message = $this.data("confirm"), // read confirmation message from custom attribute
		url = $this.attr("href"); // read AJAX URL with parameters from HREF attribute on the link

	if(confirm(confirm_message)) // if user confirmed operation, then...
	{
		// perform AJAX request
		$("#news-comments-grid").yiiGridView("update",
		{
			type	: "POST", // importatnt! we only allow POST in filters()
			dataType: "json",
			url		: url,
			success	: function(data)
			{
				console.log("Success:", data);
				$("#news-comments-grid").yiiGridView("update"); // refresh gridview via AJAX
			},
			error	: function(xhr)
			{
				console.log("Error:", xhr);
			}
		});
	}
}';

```

#Using `CHtml::ajaxButton` to process ajax request

First, check if a current user has `siteModerator` role, if so, then show ajax button in view.
When request success, we check response code, if it is `200` - OK, then remove `Wait moderation` label and `Publish comment` button.

```php
<?php
echo '<span class="label label-warning comment-status-' . $comment->id; . '"' . Yii::t( 'myApp', 'Wait moderation' ); . '</span>';
if ( Yii::app()->authManager->checkAccess( 'siteModerator', Yii::app()->user->id ) )
{
    echo CHtml::ajaxButton(
        Yii::t( 'myApp', 'Publish comment' ),
        [ 'approveComment', 'comment_id' => $comment->id ], // URL: ?r=myCtrl/approveComment&comment_id=123
        [
            'dataType' => 'json',
            'success'  => 'js:function(response)
                {
                    console.log("Approve comment response:", response);
                    if(response && response.code==200)
                    {
                        $(".comment-status-' . $comment->id . '").remove();
                        $(".approve-link-' . $comment->id . '").remove();
                    }
                }',
        ],
        [ 'class' => 'btn btn-info btn-xs approve-link-' . $comment->id ]
    );
}
```

Create `approveComment` action in `MyCtrlController`:

```php
<?php
class MyCtrlController extends Controller {
	// ...
	public function actionApproveComment( $comment_id )
	{
		if ( Yii::app()->request->isAjaxRequest )
		{
		    // get model by ID
			$comment = NewsComments::model()->findByPk( $comment_id );
			if ( $comment ) // if found...
			{
				$comment->scenario = 'approve'; // set scenario
				$comment->status   = 1; // approve
				if ( $comment->save() ) // save
					echo CJSON::encode( [ 'code' => '200', ] ); // OK status
				else
					echo CJSON::encode( $comment->getErrors() ); // errors
			}
		}
	}
}
