Also set scenario, this is useful when for example you don't want to validate all fields (e.g. captcha verifyCode field).
```php
<?php
class NewsComments extends CActiveRecord{
	// ...
	public function rules()
	{
		return array(
			[ 'news_id, author, text', 'required' ],
			[ 'news_id, status', 'numerical', 'integerOnly' => true ],
			[ 'author', 'length', 'max' => 50 ],
			[ 'verifyCode', 'captcha', 'allowEmpty' => !CCaptcha::checkRequirements(), 'except' => 'approve' ], // do not validate this attribute on approve scenario
			[ 'id, news_id, author, text, status, created_at, updated_at', 'safe', 'on' => 'search' ],
		);
	}
}
